-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">342</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":342,\"repo\":\"arnobl/latexdraw\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->(<code>Linux</code>): \"A vector drawing editor for LaTeX.\"</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:44:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization and Graph Making</h2><h3>Graph Making</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.texample.net/tikz/\">TikZ</a>(<code>LaTeX</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:44:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IlFk3cyRB0Y&#x26;list=PLM-Y_YQmMEqD2EWfWpSbiV3WgShRRW3FE&#x26;index=7\">Vue.js VideoTutoral Series in Spanish (3-8-2016)</a> on YouTube by Juan Andrés Núñez</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:31:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"#static-site-generator\">Static Site Generator</a>: For more please refer to <a href=\"#static-site-generator\">Static Site Generator</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:21:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://25.io/mou/\">Mou</a>(<code>Mac</code>): Mou used to be the best Markdown editor on Mac. It is not bad but DO NOT preorder Mou 1.0. This project is dead, unofficially. <a href=\"http://matrix.sspai.com/p/c7a3c9c0\">了解为什么死掉，请阅读此文。</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:15:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://markdownpad.com/\">MarkdownPad</a> (<code>Win</code>): If you have no bad feelings about .NET, this is pretty good.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:15:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/retext-project/retext\">ReText</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/retext-project/retext\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1415,\"repo\":\"retext-project/retext\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> (<code>Mac</code>,<code>Win</code>,<code>Linux</code>): ReText one of the best, even on Linux. It also supports reStructuredText input.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:15:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.madoko.net/\">Madoko</a> (<code>Cloud</code>): <strong>LaTeX</strong> × Markdown ²</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:15:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Hosting</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.aerobatic.com/\">Aerobatic</a>: A powerful alternative to GitHub Pages.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Hosting</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://surge.sh/\">Surge</a>: One command upload your static website to make it live. Surge also integrates GitHub hooks.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://jekyllrb.com/\">Jekyll</a> (Written in <code>Ruby</code>)(<code>Markdown</code>): Jekyll is the most widely used one. The best part about Jekyll is that one just deploy to GitHub Pages by pushing the source to GitHub.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://octopress.org/\">Octopress</a> (Written in <code>Ruby</code>)(<code>Markdown</code>): Octopress is easier to use compared with Jekyll while being somewhat compatible with Jekyll.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hexo.io/\">Hexo</a> (Written in <code>Node.js</code>)(<code>Markdown</code>): \"A fast, simple &#x26; powerful blog framework\" as they say on their website. It supports GFM.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://getpelican.com\">Pelican</a> (Written in <code>Python</code>)(<code>reStructuredText</code>,<code>Markdown</code>,<code>AsciiDoc</code>): Pelican is a modularized framework and is perfect for blogging.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wting/pelican-svbtle\">Pelican Svbtle Theme</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wting/pelican-svbtle\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">151</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":151,\"repo\":\"wting/pelican-svbtle\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://getnikola.com/\">Nikola</a> (Written in <code>Python</code>)(<code>reStructuredText</code>,<code>Markdown</code>,<code>IPython Notebook/Jupyter</code>,<code>PHP</code>, etc): It takes in multiple input formats including reStructuredText and many others.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Static Site Generator</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://gohugo.io/\">Hugo</a>(Written in <code>Go</code>)(<code>Markdown</code>): Easy to use and really fast. It also supports more input formats through plugins.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h3>Keep The Notes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Some other <a href=\"#static-generator\">static site generators</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T23:07:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://marxi.co/\">Marxico</a>(<code>Cloud</code>,<code>Mac</code>,<code>Win</code>,<code>Chrome</code>): Markdown editor that integrates with Evernote, generates pdf and works offline. <a href=\"https://maxiang.io/\">马克飞象</a>(<code>Cloud</code>,<code>Mac</code>,<code>Win</code>,<code>Chrome</code>) is the Chinese version。</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:41:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.typora.io/\">typora</a>(<code>Mac</code>,<code>Win</code>):  Beautiful UI and in-situ live preview.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:41:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pad.haroopress.com/\">Haroopad</a>(<code>Mac</code>,<code>Win</code>,<code>Linux</code>): A powerful github flavored markdown editor with useful extensions. Math (mathjax) is supported.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:41:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zybuluo.com/mdeditor\">CMD markdown</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): CMD is a Markdown editor with math (MathJax) support. What is special is that it keeps edit history. (Chinese UI.)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.penflip.com/\">Penflip</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): Penflip is designed to be a GitHub for writers. It is Markdown-based and git like without math support.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.authorea.com/\">Authorea</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): A much more powerful Markdown and LaTeX online editor that can be used to produce nice academic papers.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://kramdown.herokuapp.com/\">Online Kramdown Editor</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): Just another Markdown editor without math support.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pandoc.herokuapp.com/\">Pandoc Markdown</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): Just another Markdown editor with math (MathJax) support.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.madoko.net/\">Madoko</a>(<code>Cloud</code>,<code>Chrome</code>): A Markdown editor with math support, where images are inserted easily with one click, while your files are saved on Dropbox, GitHub, OneDrive or local disk. It generates pdf and HTML page and works offline using browser's local storage. One can even import LaTeX files.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note Taking</h2><h4>Markdown</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://jbt.github.io/markdown-editor/\">jbt/markdown-editor</a>(<code>Cloud</code>): Just another online Markdown editor without math support.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T22:17:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"h4cc/awesome-elixir","categoryHTML":"<h2>Geolocation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nazipov/ip2location-elixir\">ip2location</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nazipov/ip2location-elixir\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15,\"repo\":\"nazipov/ip2location-elixir\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An Elixir library for IP2Location database.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:58:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Publishing and Sharing</h2><h3>Writing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gitbook.com/\">Gitbook</a>: A new but promising tool for HTML, pdf, and epub with both online editors and local editors. Plugins like quizzes and math can be helpful to writing science.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:56:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>Softwares</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ipython.org/notebook.html\">iPython Notebook</a> (<code>Python</code>): a useful tool for inline calculation, making graphs and writing notes.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wakari.io/\">wakari.io</a> is a comercial one mostly aimed for data analysis.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ptone/jiffylab\">jiffylab</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ptone/jiffylab\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">187</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":187,\"repo\":\"ptone/jiffylab\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> is an open source one but not that well done.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/writefaruq/supervised-ipython-nbserver\">supervised-ipython-nbserver</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/writefaruq/supervised-ipython-nbserver\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6,\"repo\":\"writefaruq/supervised-ipython-nbserver\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> is a multiuser version of notebook using Django/Pinax.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:56:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Pacifier</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://coffitivity.com/\">Coffitivity</a>(<code>iOS</code>, <code>Android</code>, <code>Web</code>, <code>Mac</code>): a rather simple but useful coffee shop noise library; premium has more three more soundtracks; elegant UI; scientific research powered</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:56:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"emptymalei/awesome-research","categoryHTML":"<h2>Pacifier</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.focusatwill.com\">focus@will</a>(<code>iOS</code>, <code>Android</code>, <code>Web</code>): music to boost your brain; paid services now</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:56:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rshipp/awesome-malware-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Threat Intelligence</h2><h3>Other Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://iplists.firehol.org/\">FireHOL IP Lists</a> - Analytics for 350+ IP lists\nwith a focus on attacks, malware and abuse. Evolution, Changes History,\nCountry Maps, Age of IPs listed, Retention Policy, Overlaps.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:27:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Studying</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.edx.org/course/subject/economics-finance\">edX Economics</a> - Introductory topics, few prerequisites.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Studying</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.khanacademy.org/economics-finance-domain\">Khan Academy: Economics</a> - Elementary topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Studying</h2><h3>Useful Materials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://economics.stackexchange.com/questions/35/what-are-the-foundational-equations-of-economics\">Foundational Equations of Economics</a> - These equations show principles behind \"thinking like an economist\". Graduate textbooks put these equiations in context.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Portals</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://repec.org/\">RePEc</a> - Web services for economic researchers: bibliography, blog aggregator, new working papers, software.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Portals</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://research.stlouisfed.org/resources.html\">Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis: Web Services</a> - A list of helpful services.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Articles and Working Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ssrn.com/en/index.cfm/ern/\">SSRN Economics</a> - Working papers, no journal publications.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://research.stlouisfed.org/fred2/\">FRED2</a> - 380,000 (macro) time series from 80 sources. Supports plugins for importing data into Excel, Stata, R, and others. Has a mobile app.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://data.worldbank.org/\">World Bank Data</a> - International macro time series. Has data import plugins.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quandl.com/\">Quandl</a> - Aggregate financial and economic data from multiple sources. Some data vendors sell their data via this service. Good integration with statistical software.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.latex-project.org/\">LaTeX</a> - Economists write in LaTeX because it handles mathematics and references better than Word or LibreOffice. If you write regularly, LaTeX is worth learning.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.ctan.org/pkg/beamer?lang=en\">Beamer</a> - A LaTeX class for presentations.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.texample.net/tikz/examples/\">TikZ</a> - An extension for drawing graphs. A <a href=\"http://cremeronline.com/LaTeX/minimaltikz.pdf\">how-to</a> and a <a href=\"http://www.texample.net/media/pgf/builds/pgfmanualCVS2012-11-04.pdf\">manual</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.lyx.org/\">LyX</a> - A free and simple editor for LaTeX.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/\">Zotero</a> - Bibliography management. Also install (a) Zotero browser plugin to import papers from RePEc to your library; (b) Zotero-LyX plugin to cite literature easily.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Useful Materials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://stats.stackexchange.com/questions/2910/how-to-efficiently-manage-a-statistical-analysis-project\">How to efficiently manage a statistical analysis project?</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Research</h2><h3>Useful Materials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>RePEc Rankings by citations\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://ideas.repec.org/top/top.person.all.html\">Top Authors</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ideas.repec.org/top/top.inst.nbcites.html\">Economic Institutions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ideas.repec.org/top/top.item.nbcites.html\">Research Items</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://logec.repec.org/scripts/itemstat.pf?type=redif-software\">Software Items</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discussions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Blogs - The most popular form of self-expression among economists. The major blog aggregators:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://econacademics.org/\">EconAcademics.org</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://economistsview.typepad.com/\">Economist's View</a> - Mark Thoma</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://delong.typepad.com/\">Grasping Reality</a> - Brad DeLong</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://marginalrevolution.com/\">Marginal Revolution</a> - Tyler Cowen and Alex Tabarrok</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.voxeu.org/\">VOX CEPR</a> - Members of CEPR</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discussions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cse.google.com/cse/publicurl?cx=002720237717066476899:i_zfef5fawa\">Economics Blog Search</a> - A Google-based search service for aforementioned blogs.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discussions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://economics.stackexchange.com/\">StackExchange Economics</a> - A Q&#x26;A website where you can ask and answer questions.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discussions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Reddit - A popular news aggregator. Has many economics-related sections, for example:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/GoodEconomics/\">/r/GoodEconomics/</a> - Selected pieces on economic issues.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/EconPapers/\">/r/EconPapers/</a> - Discussing economic papers.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Undergraduate</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>University rankings - May help in choosing a college.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/university-subject-rankings/2016/economics-econometrics#sorting=rank+region=+country=+faculty=+stars=false+search=\">QS World University Rankings by Subject 2016 - Economics &#x26; Econometrics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.shanghairanking.com/SubjectEcoBus2015.html\">Academic Ranking of World Universities in Economics / Business</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Faculty</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://econjobmarket.org/postings.php\">Econ Jobs Postings</a> - List of academic job openings.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-31T21:08:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antontarasenko/awesome-economics","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Faculty</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a 